<br>
Point hoarding is not worse than wasteful spending.  There is a balance.  If you know you're going to buy RZ Time shoulders, you shouldn't pick up a Saryrm Time shoulder.<br>
<br>
Here's a system I worked out with people in my guild and I think it rocks (I'm biased).<br>
<br>
1.  Events are assigned MIN and MAX prices<br>
2.  All loot dropping in that event are called at the MAX price<br>
3.  If more than 1 person says &quot;I want that&quot;, total points are used to determine winner<br>
4.  If nobody wants at MAX price, the loot is reduced 50 points and is open to all participants<br>
5.  The item continues to be reduced 50 points until somebody puts in or it reaches MIN<br>
6.  Points are only used in determining the winner if the item is bid at MAX<br>
<br>
So for example, Time Tier 2 is 50MIN and 200MAX.<br>
Gauntlets drop, we have 50 people there.  The gaunts are called at 200.  Nobody wants, so they get dropped to 150.  Still, nobody wants, so they get dropped to 100.  Bob (has 150points) and Tom(has 600points) both put in.  But, since it wasn't called at MAX, we just /rand 1 2<br>
<br>
Next, the Earring drops in Tier 2.  It's called at 200MAX.  Both Bob(has 150points) and Tom (has 500points) want it.  Tom automatically wins since it was called at MAX points.<br>
<br>
So, we have 50 people there and 300 points where used.  Each person gets 6 points.<br>
<br>
There ya go.  We did a trial of this system and after having it in practice the &quot;make it perm vote&quot; went something like 60 to 5 in favor of keeping.<br>
<br>
I like it.  It solves rot, it solves hoarding, and it allows newer people to quickly gear up on low end gear without going deep negative. <p><IMG SRC=http://www.databenchmark.com/sigs/OrmeFF.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=suladasbardspeed>Suladas Bardspeed</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 309<br> <font color=#330000>(6/5/04 12:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19464.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sigh, ELP vs DKP?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Point systems work best when people do not horde points. Saving points up for an upgrade is one thing, but passing up on an amulet of crystal dreams vs your neck is....  <br>
