<br>
My guilds current system uses a closed bid, semi-fixed amount system.  /Tells are taken for bid amounts (rot, decent, good, uber).  Rot items cost 1 point, decent 3, good 6, and uber is 20+ (minimum of 20, max depends on several factors, but normally most/all current points).  Although points you have to spend is in 1 pool, there are point totals for each bid class so the person with the most points won't necessarly win the item.  Points are earned based on raid attendence the previous week.  Officer corruption is non-existant since all point totals and calculations are posted on the website.  If 2 people bid uber on a item, it is simple to see who will win.  Nothing rots as it will go to recruits if need be.  Point hoarding is also rare as those people who have a lot of points are saving for a specific item or they need no upgrades from current content.<br>
