ELP ( Event Lotto Points ) is a system started in October of 2000 by the guild Inner Circle. At its' heart it's a system where members earn points for successfully defeating a boss mob and then can bid, auction style, these points to earn loot. Bonus ELP was awarded for first kills or particularly onerous encounters. As well the ELP earned per mob dropped as the encounter became more routine.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
To elaborate, ELP was a bid system introduced by Inner Circle.  DKP was a fixed priced system, and I'm not positive who invented it, but Afterlife at least helped popularize it.<br>
<br>
Because of this, at the time, guilds that adopted bidding systems tended to use the acronym ELP (or another acronym such as the abbreviation of the guild followed by the letter P).  Guilds that adopted fixed point systems used the abbreviation DKP.  (ELP-system meant bidding system, and DKP-system meant fixed-point system.)<br>
<br>
As time progressed, guilds on Xegony (such as my current one) started using the abbreviation ELP even if they used a fixed point system.  Probably just because everyone on the server refered to earning and spending ELP, so ELP just became shorthand (or perhaps long-hand) for points.<br>
<br>
And by the sound of it, others elsewhere started using DKP even if they used a bid system.  The word &quot;DKP-bidding&quot; still makes me do a double-take though.<br>
<br>
(It is rather odd that DKP meant fixed-price, as the factor that gives &quot;DKP&quot; it's name isn't the fixed bidding, but the fact that your points came from killing certain large creatures, with a predetermined value for killing each.  I guess the method of receiving points isn't considered quite as central as the method of picking a winner for loot.  And when I became aware of DKP, the looting-list idea for such camps as FBSS was becoming popular, and fixed-point systems are a fairly natural extension of this.)<br>
<br>
Anyway, when people ask DKP vs. ELP, they are asking for a discussion of fixed cost vs. bidding loot distribution systems.<br>
<br>
- Lall<br>
Bold Bardess with 112 Melodic Tools<br>
Shards of Avalon, Xegony. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=llanmal>Llanmal</A> at: 6/7/04 12:17 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=raiddinn>Raiddinn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 246<br> <font color=#330000>(6/8/04 9:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19464.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ~</span><hr size=1> Never heard anyone ever say ELP on RZ, its either DKP, DKP bidding, or loot council, mostly loot council.<br>
