DKP earned on ( roughly ) hour basis.<br>
DKP balanced in vs out every two weeks ( gain x hours during a 14 day period, at end of the period, each hour is converted to (total guild dkp gained / total guild hours earned) dkp.<br>
Highest dkp wins items.<br>
<br>
Benefits: Impartial except during the time of pricing ( done by officers ). No collusion to lower prices for single class items etc. The time balancing encourages people to show up for all raids in an easy way.<br>
Zerosum system means its stable over time ( relatively ), as long as pricing is done decently well.<br>
<br>
Downsides: Being high in dkp is important if you want certain rare pieces. Stuff will rot earlier than in a system with flexible prices. Pricing new stuff correctly is important ( we had one major flaw with aten neck being cheap, which led to everyone saving up for it, but EP and time sofar have been more balanced... can maybe see songblade etc being a problem in time, but none dropped yet ).<br>
<br>
Since noone really complains about the system I guess it works. We used to use a fixed pricing, whatever raid gains in dkp = dkp earned for that raid-system, but this caused VT raids ( which is where we were at the time ) to give 15 dkp and PoP raids to give 2 or so, which clearly was a bad idea ( one raid = more dkp than an entire week of pop progression attempts ). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mugwye>Mugwye</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#330000>(6/10/04 10:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19464.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> I am in a guild that has been around for around 3 years and have made the elementals.  We are considered a family guild that raids (RL&gt;EQ)<br>
